metadata.name: History
metadata.description:
Title: History 
Artist: Lisa Llarena
Edition: 1/1 
4000 x 6000 px 

Collection: Braille 

I walked through the woods finding these tiny landscapes in a meditative state, feeling everything fully. All the exquisite, complex textures so raw and real, reminding me that things are beautiful as they are and how we found them. 

History written, an irreversible record of all that has transpired and touched them. Each event leaving a mark—every ray of sunshine, every drop of rain. Stories found in scars, jagged edges, the parts that turn brittle or hard, and what persists and remains. 

—
